## [1] 1599   13

The datasets to be explores describing a Wine Quality Red. We have 13 variables and 1,599 red wines based on their chemical properties, the quality score between 0 (very bad) and 10 (very excellent).

Reflection

I started by exploring each variable individually plot then created 2 variable plot then 3 variables plot.

The limitations I faced was in learning the new language “R”. Some limitations in this dataset when I try to understand information about the composition of wine. When adding a third dimension in the multivariate plots it becomes harder to grasp trends. When exploring with such a dataset i have a challenge that choose in which direction to do our exploration, but after read the description file that help me like at (volatile acidity: the amount of Acetic Acid in wine, which at too high levels can lead to an unpleasant, vinegar taste). The struggles that i went through is quality was positively correlated with Alcohol feature and negatively correlated with Volatile Acidity and Residual Sugar.

Finally, in future work could be build a use classification models to classifier the wine quality based on the chemical attributes. We could improve the quality of our analysis by collecting more data and more information about the composition of wine to informs the commentary like how the components of wine affect the taste of wine.
